==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mure
<hw>Mure</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Mured</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>murer</ets>,
L. <ets>murare</ets>. See <er>Mure</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To
inclose in walls; to wall; to immure; to shut up.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The five kings are <qex>mured</qex> in a cave.</q> <rj><qau>John.
x. (Heading).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Murenger</ent>⟦br⟧
